<item>
            <title>[LU-6539] incorrect integer format string used for short type </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6539</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;cppcheck found an incorrect format string being used for a short type:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Checking lustre/quota/lquota_entry.c...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;lustre/quota/lquota_entry.c:219&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: (warning) %u in format string (no. 1) requires &apos;unsigned int&apos; but the argument type is &apos;short&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;struct lquota_site *lquota_site_alloc(const struct lu_env *env, void *parent,&lt;br/&gt;
                                      bool is_master, short qtype,&lt;br/&gt;
                                      struct lquota_entry_operations *ops)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sprintf(hashname, &quot;LQUOTA_HASH%u&quot;, qtype);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;needs to be %hu (or %hd)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Build on Ubuntu 15.04, static analysis check build with current cppcheck</environment>
